o]]|f}}, {{t+|pt|porco|m}}\n* Romani:\n*: Kalo Finnish Romani: {{t|rmf|baliȟnesko mas}}\n* Romanian: {{t|ro|[[carne]] [[de]] [[porc]]}}, {{t+|ro|porc|m}}\n* Romansh: {{t|rm|charn-portg|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|свини́на|f}}\n* Sami:\n*: Lule Sami: {{t|smj|svijnebierggo}}\n* Samoan: {{t-needed|sm}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|feòil-muice|f}}, {{t|gd|muicfheòil|f}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|свињетина|f}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|svinjetina|f}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|bravčové|n}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|svinjina|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|cerdo|m}}, {{t+|es|puerco|m}}, {{t|es|[[carne]] [[de]] [[chancho]]|m}}, {{t|es|matagón|m}} {{q|El Salvador}}\n* Sranan Tongo: {{t|srn|agumeti}}\n* Swahili: {{t|sw|kitimoto}}, {{t|sw|[[nyama]] ya [[nguruwe]]}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|fläsk|n}}, {{t+|sv|fläskkött|n}}, {{t+|sv|griskött|n}}, {{t|sv|svinkött|n}}\n* Tajik: {{t|tg|[[гӯшт|гӯшти]] [[хуг]]}}, {{t+|tg|хуг}}\n* Taos: {{t|twf|kùcitúone}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|หมู}}, {{t|th|[[เนื้อ]][[หมู]]|tr=nʉ́ʉa mǔu}}\n*: Northern Thai: {{t|nod|ᨶᩮᩬᩨ᩶ᩋᩉ᩠ᨾᩪ}}, {{t|nod|ᩉ᩠ᨾᩪ}}\n* Tongan: {{t|to|puaka}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|domuz eti}}, {{t+|tr|domuz}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|свини́на|f}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|[[سُؤَر]] [[کا]] [[گوشْت]]|m}}, {{t|ur|سُؤَر|m}}\n* Uyghur: {{t|ug|[[چوشقا]] [[گۆش|گۆشى]]}}, {{t|ug|چوشقا}}\n* Uzbek: {{t|uz|[[choʻchqa]] [[goʻsht|goʻshti]]}}, {{t+|uz|choʻchqa}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t|vi|[[thịt]] [[heo]]}}, {{t|vi|[[thịt]] [[lợn]]}}\n* Volapük: {{t|vo|svinamit}}\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|porc|m}}, {{q|usually bacon in particular}} {{t|cy|cig moch|m}}\n* Yao (Africa): {{t|yao|liguluŵe|5}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|שװײַן|m}}\n* Zazaki: {{t|zza|gosté xozi}}\n* Zhuang: {{t|za|[[noh]] [[mou]]}}\n* Zigula: {{t|ziw|nguluwe|9}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|opportunist political appropriation}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|valfläsk|n}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n=====See also=====\n* {{l|en|bacon}}\n* {{l|en|ham}}\n* {{l|en|pig}}\n* {{l|en|porcupine}}\n* {{l|en|swine}}\n\n====Verb====\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive|slang|vulgar|usually|of a male}} To have sex with (someone).\n#: {{syn|en|Thesaurus:copulate with}}\n#* {{quote-av|en|medium=motion picture|role=Boon|actor=Peter Riegert|title=Animal House|year=1978|publisher=Universal Pictures|author=Harold Ramis; Douglas Kenney; Chris Miller|passage=Marlene! Don't tell me you're gonna '''pork''' Marlene Desmond!}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=12 Feb 89|volume=16|number=30|journal=Gay Community News|page=9|title=Fun With The Electro-Lux And Other Masturbation Stories|author=Vanessa Nemeth;Stephanie Poggi|text=You know, I can't remember just how I discovered doorknobs, but as a teenager  I used to '''pork''' myself on a particular one — a nice, smooth round one — from time to time.}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\n{{blend|en|pin|fork}}.\n\n====Noun====\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{lb|en|chess}} A [[position]] in which a player's [[piece]]s are both [[pin]]ned and [[fork]]ed at the same time.\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n\n{{topics|en|Law enforcement|Meats|Sex}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|enm|porc|porke}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{etymon|enm|:bor|fro:porc}}\n{{bor+|enm|fro|porc|t=pig}}, from {{der|enm|la|porcus}}; compare {{m|enm|farowen}}. {{etydate|c|1300}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|enm|/pɔrk/|/pɔːrk/}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{enm-noun|porkes}}\n\n# {{l|en|pork}} {{gloss|[[pig]] [[meat]]}}\n# [[swine]], [[pig]]\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|en|pork}}\n* {{desc|gmw-msc|pork|porc|porck}}\n** {{desc|sco|pork}}\n** {{desc|scz|purk}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:MED Online|entry=pork(e|pos=n|id=MED34054|accessdate=2018-04-03}}\n* {{R:enm:Bliss:1969|41|187}}\n\n{{C|enm|Livestock|Meats}}\n\n==Spanish==\n\n===Conjunction===\n{{head|es|conjunction}}\n\n# {{lb|es|internet slang}} {{abbrev of|es|porque}}"}}